        <div>
          <span class="eyebrow">The Short Version</span>
          <h2 class="mt-5">A mortgage license is a defined checklist &mdash; not a mystery</h2>
          <p class="lede">Education, exam, application, background and credit checks, sponsorship. Five things. Finish them in order and you're licensed.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="body-text">
          <p>If you've been searching how to get a mortgage license, the honest answer is that the path is well-defined and the same for everyone. The license that lets you originate loans is the individual mortgage loan originator (MLO) license, issued through the <a class="inline-link" href="https://nmlsconsumeraccess.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">NMLS</a> under the federal <a class="inline-link" href="https://www.consumerfinance.gov/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">SAFE Act of 2008</a>.</p>
          <p>This page owns the licensing detail for the whole guide: the NMLS requirements, the pre-licensure education, the costs, the timeline, and renewal. The <a class="inline-link" href="/mortgage-career/safe-mlo-exam/">SAFE MLO exam guide</a> covers the test itself, and the role pages explain what you do once licensed &mdash; <a class="inline-link" href="/mortgage-career/loan-officer/">become a loan officer</a> or <a class="inline-link" href="/mortgage-career/mortgage-broker/">become a mortgage broker</a>.</p>
          <p>Below: the exact requirements, what a mortgage license costs, how long it takes, and how renewal works.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
